The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Seven held for murder outside mall
                                                                            Tuesday , November 10 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            Seven held for murder outside mall
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Seven persons were arrested on Monday on the charge of murdering a 30-year-old man whose body was found outside Sreeram Arcade on Saturday afternoon.         
	An officer of New Market police station said the man, yet to be identified, was beaten to death for allegedly stealing a cellphone and Rs 170 last month from his co-worker in a nearby snack shop.         
	The accused  Saddam Hussain, Rabi Das, Mohammad Pervez, his mother Salma Khatoon, Mohammad Guddu, Gopal Singh alias Chhotu and Mohammad Pappu  were produced in court and remanded in police custody.        
	Footage recorded by closed-circuit cameras installed at Sreeram Arcade and The Oberoi Grand showed these people beating up the victim. He was frail and succumbed to his injuries. We are interrogating the accused to find out the name and address of the man, said an investigator.         
	According to the police, the victim had worked in the snack shop owned by Gopal Singh till a month and a half back.        
	He went missing after stealing Rs 170 and a cellphone from his co-worker Saddam Hussain. On Saturday, Saddam, Rabi, Pervez and Guddu saw him sitting on the bank of Manohar Das Tarag, on the other side of Jawaharlal Nehru Road, added the officer.        
	The four dragged him to the snack shop, located behind Sreeram Arcade, and allegedly started beating him up. They were later joined by Mohammad Shahid, who is absconding, Salma Khatoon, Gopal Singh and Mohammad Pappu, said an officer.        
	A probe is on to ascertain the exact reason why the youth was killed, added the officer.                                                                                                                                                                           
